            <h2 class="text-primary text-center mt-5">About the Assignment project</h2>
            <p class="text-center ">In this assignment, I will build a server using NodeJs. My server will listen
                on port 5500.</p>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-12">
                    <p>The Node.js application is a simple web server designed to meet specific requirements. It
                        utilizes the http module to create an HTTP server that listens on port 5500. The server has a
                        basic routing system that handles different URL paths and generates dynamic HTML content for
                        each page.</p>

                    <p>The application includes the following features:</p>

                    <ol>
                        <li><strong>Home Page (/):</strong> Displays a message indicating that it is the Home Page.</li>
                        <li><strong>About Page (/about):</strong> Displays a message indicating that it is the About
                            Page.</li>
                        <li><strong>Contact Page (/contact):</strong> Displays a message indicating that it is the
                            Contact Page.</li>
                        <li><strong>File Write Page (/file-write):</strong> Creates a file named "demo.txt" and writes
                            the text "hello world" into it.</li>
                        <li><strong>File Upload Page (/file-upload):</strong> Provides a placeholder for file upload
                            functionality using the Multer middleware. Users can customize this page to handle file
                            uploads as needed.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <p>The application dynamically generates HTML content based on the requested URL, and a common menu
                        is included on each page for navigation. The HTML content is sent to the client as the server's
                        response, providing a simple and functional web server with routing capabilities.</p>


